The paper discusses the use of data mining techniques for analyzing brain disorder data, which involves high-dimensional tensor representations and brain connectivity networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
